Name: transient neonatal diabetes mellitus
Definition: A neonatal diabetes mellitus characterized by hyperglycemia during the neonatal period that remits during infancy but recurs in later life in most patients.

Name: neonatal diabetes mellitus with congenital hypothyroidism
Definition: A neonatal diabetes mellitus characterized by intrauterine growth retardation

Name: permanent neonatal diabetes mellitus
Definition: A neonatal diabetes mellitus that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the glucokinase gene (GCK)
